    <middle>
        <section title="Introduction">
            <t>
		<xref target="I-D.ietf-opsawg-tacacs">The TACACS+ Protocol</xref> provides device administration for routers, network access servers and other networked computing devices via one or more centralized servers.
		The protocol carries authentication, authorization and accounting information for TACACS+ clients.
		While this information is highly sensitive, TACACS+ lacks modern and suitable privacy, integrity and authentication of the connection and network traffic between the server and client.
		Its existing mechanism is weak, leaving the protocol highly susceptible to Man in the Middle (MitM) attacks.
            </t>
            <t>
		To address these flaws, this document updates <xref target="I-D.ietf-opsawg-tacacs">The TACACS+ Protocol</xref> to support <xref target="RFC8446">TLS</xref> authentication and encryption, and deprecates the use of its former mechanisms.
            </t>
        </section>

